Name: A Very Supernatural Christmas
Description: In this Christmas episode, Sam and Dean track an "anti-Santa" who abducts victims through chimneys. Dean wants to celebrate as they used to, but Sam faces the reality that it might be their last Christmas together.

Name: It's the Great Pumpkin, Sam Winchester
Description: Sam and Dean investigate mysterious deaths in a town and uncover a witch's plan to summon an ancient and dangerous demon.

Name: My Bloody Valentine
Description: Castiel assists Sam and Dean as they track down Cupid, who is responsible for a string of love-related killings on Valentine's Day.

Name: Love Hurts
Description: In this Valentine's Day-themed episode, Sam and Dean investigate a series of murders caused by an ancient curse that marks its victims for death.

Name: Last Holiday
Description: Dean and Sam find a wood nymph living in their bunker, who will do whatever it takes to protect her "family".

Name: The Man in the Fallout Shelter
Description: The gang is quarantined in the lab for Christmas and investigates a skeleton found in a fallout shelter.

Name: Mummy in the Maze
Description: Booth and Bones investigate the discovery of two mummified girls and search for a missing girl while checking a fun house, Halloween maze, and church charity for leads.

Name: The Santa in the Slush
Description: Brennan and Booth investigate the death of a Santa while trying to make the holiday special for their loved ones: Bones attempts to fulfill her father's Christmas wishes, while Booth copes with not being with his son.

Name: The Goop on the Girl
Description: Brennan and Booth investigate a Santa Claus who blew himself up during a bank robbery. Meanwhile, Brennan plans to spend Christmas in El Salvador, but her father convinces her to stay with Margaret, a distant relative.

Name: High Treason in the Holiday Season
Description: A journalist investigating corruption is found dead. Hodgins becomes paranoid over the investigation being monitored. The team gathers for Thanksgiving.

Name: Lexmas
Description: On Christmas Eve, Lex is shot by a couple during a car-jacking and has to undergo surgery to prevent permanent paralysis. While he's under, Lex dreams of an alternate future with Lana. Meanwhile, Clark helps Chloe deliver Christmas presents to underprivileged children.

Name: Gemini
Description: As Christmas approaches, Lois receives a call that Chloe is attached to a bomb unless she reports on Lex's experiments. Chloe reveals her healing powers to Jimmy while trapped in an elevator. Clark returns from the Fortress of Solitude and wants to take down Lex with Lana's help.

Name: Damned if You Do
Description: House treats a nun for dermatitis and asthma but his diagnosis and treatment may have been wrong, leading to a life-threatening situation.

Name: Merry Little Christmas
Description: Wilson proposes a deal to House with Cuddy's support, while the team struggles with a difficult case and keeps seeking House's opinion despite his unavailability.

Name: Insensitive
Description: House interferes with relationships on Valentine's Day while trying to diagnose a teenage patient who cannot feel pain due to a genetic condition.

Name: It's a Wonderful Lie
Description: House becomes preoccupied with a mother and daughter who can't lie and uses Christmas to create tension among his team.

Name: Joy to the World
Description: A teen collapses on stage, leading to a surprise for Cuddy. Wilson persuades House to be kinder to patients during the holidays. Foreman and Thirteen have trouble with a trial patient dropping out.

Name: Ignorance is Bliss
Description: A high IQ courier collapses at a bookstore, while House continues his antics to gain Cuddy's attention. The situation escalates when Chase punches House.

Name: My Day Off
Description: On Thanksgiving, J.D. gets diagnosed with appendicitis at Sacred Heart. Dr. Cox wants to impress his former mentor, Dr. Benson. Elliot attempts to be a more empathetic doctor.

Name: My Own Personal Jesus
Description: On Christmas, only Turk is in a festive mood. Cox asks J.D. to film a friend's baby's birth, but things don't go as planned.

Name: My Best Moment
Description: J.D. speaks to a group of pre-med students but decides to talk about his best experiences as a doctor.

Name: The One Where Underdog Gets Away
Description: The group is locked out of Monica and Rachel's apartment, causing their Thanksgiving plans to go wrong.

Name: The One with the Candy Hearts
Description: On Valentine's Day, Ross coincidentally dines in the same restaurant as Carol and Susan. Joey arranges a date for Chandler with Janice, while the girls burn keepsakes from past relationships.

Name: The One with Phoebe’s Dad
Description: Phoebe locates her father but is uncertain about whether to meet him or not.

Name: The One Where Ross and Rachel… You Know
Description: Monica develops a crush on her parents' friend while catering for him. Ross and Rachel have their first date. Joey and Chandler are reluctant to give up their new TV and armchairs.

Name: The One with the Football
Description: Monica and Ross's childhood rivalry causes a delay in Thanksgiving dinner as the group plays a game of touch football.

Name: The One Where Rachel Quits
Description: Ross accidentally breaks a little girl's leg and helps her sell cookies, which triggers Monica's past obsession. Rachel resigns from her job at Central Perk. Joey's Christmas tree selling clashes with Phoebe's beliefs.

Name: The One Where Ross and Rachel Take a Break
Description: After a fight with Rachel, Ross finds comfort in another woman's arms at a party. Phoebe's date requires an interpreter to communicate.

Name: The One with Chandler in a Box
Description: Chandler lies in a wooden box for six hours to apologize to Joey. Monica gets ice in her eye and is treated by Richard's son. Rachel's gift-giving habit is exposed.

Name: The One with the Girl from Poughkeepsie
Description: Monica hires Joey to demonstrate her authority to the kitchen staff by firing him. Chandler's attempt to set Rachel up with a co-worker fails, and Ross can't decide between two girls.

Name: The One with All the Thanksgivings
Description: The group recalls and shares their worst Thanksgiving experiences with each other.

Name: The One with the Inappropriate Sister
Description: Ross causes chaos in Chandler and Joey's lives out of boredom. Rachel is uneasy about Danny's close bond with his sister. Phoebe faces difficulties while collecting donations for the needy during Christmas.

Name: The One Where Everybody Finds Out
Description: Phoebe and Rachel discover Monica and Chandler's secret relationship and try to make them confess.

Name: The One Where Ross Got High
Description: Ross discloses why Jack and Judy dislike Chandler. Rachel attempts to make dessert for the group. Joey and Ross try to skip Thanksgiving with Janine and her dancer friends.

Name: The One with the Routine
Description: Joey tries to kiss Janine on the set of "Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve," and Monica and Ross perform their high school dance routine. Rachel, Phoebe, and Chandler search for Monica's Christmas gifts.

Name: The One With Unagi
Description: Rachel and Phoebe enroll in self-defense classes. Chandler and Monica exchange homemade Valentine's Day gifts. Joey participates in medical research to earn money.

Name: The One Where Chandler Doesn't Like Dogs
Description: Ross struggles to name all 50 states during a game, Joey ruins Rachel's chances with Tag during Thanksgiving dinner, and Phoebe sneaks a dog into the apartment, making Chandler nervous.

Name: The One with the Holiday Armadillo
Description: Ross wants to introduce Ben to Hanukkah, and Phoebe must drive a wedge between Rachel and Joey to entice her to move back into their refurbished apartment.

Name: The One with the Rumor
Description: Monica invites an old school friend, Will, to Thanksgiving dinner, unaware that he has a grudge against Rachel.

Name: The One with Ross's Step Forward
Description: Ross's new girlfriend wants to send out Christmas cards featuring a photo of them together, but Ross isn't sure he's ready to take that step yet.

Name: The One With The Birthing Video
Description: Phoebe gives Joey a happy dog to cheer him up. Monica accidentally gives Chandler a graphic birthing video instead of a romantic movie. Ross's girlfriend discovers Rachel is living with him.

Name: The One with Rachel's Other Sister
Description: Rachel's sister visits on Thanksgiving, causing arguments.

Name: The One with Christmas in Tulsa
Description: Chandler is sent to Tulsa for Christmas by his company, leaving Monica worried about his fidelity with a former Miss Oklahoma runner-up. Chandler returns early and announces he quit his job.

Name: The One with the Late Thanksgiving
Description: Monica and Chandler agree to host Thanksgiving, but Joey, Ross, Rachel, and Phoebe arrive an hour late for dinner.

Name: The One with Phoebe's Wedding
Description: Phoebe and Mike's wedding preparations go awry as last-minute issues arise.

Name: Halloween
Description: At a Halloween party, the gang sports various costumes, but Kelly's revealing outfit stands out. David meets with Scott and Brandon loses his twin niece and nephew while trick-or-treating.

Name: A Walsh Family Christmas
Description: Steve discovers the truth about his biological parents, while Dylan visits his imprisoned father. Brenda's homeless guest brings joy to the house, and Brandon and Emily establish a new friendship.

Name: Baby Makes Five
Description: On St. Valentine's Day, Dylan plans a memorable evening for Brenda while Kelly and David work to repair their parents' relationship.

Name: The Kindness of Strangers
Description: On a rainy Thanksgiving, Brandon invites homeless man Jack Canner over, while Steve breaks the news of his expulsion to his mother during a TV shoot in Santa Barbara.

Name: It's a Totally Happening Life
Description: Mysterious angels intervene and prevent a bus and a truck from crashing. Meanwhile, Dylan is asked to play Santa Claus for a group of underprivileged children.

Name: Radar Love
Description: Brandon reunites with Emily in San Francisco for Thanksgiving. Dylan agrees to dine with the Walshes, but Kelly causes a scene. Andrea is hesitant to attend Dan's parents' party but gives Jesse her address.

Name: Somewhere in the World It's Christmas
Description: The Walsh family's Hawaiian trip gets disrupted due to a plane malfunction. Dylan receives a surprise visit from a woman who claims to be Jack McKay's mistress with her daughter. David is hostile towards Donna due to his sexual frustration.

Name: Things That Go Bang in the Night
Description: Donna is spooked when her two love interests, Ray and Griffin, meet at a Halloween party. Valerie considers leaving town but stays after learning of her mother's breakdown.

Name: Christmas Comes This Time Each Year
Description: Felice tests Ray's love for Donna by offering him money to stop seeing her; LuAnn goes Christmas shopping with Donna. Jesse and Andrea's differing family traditions cause tension. David meets Clare's father at a Christmas party and bonds over music.

Name: You Gotta Have Heart
Description: Steve tries to book "Jade" for a Valentine's Day telethon at the Peach Pit After Dark. Brandon temporarily distracts Kelly from her work with Professor Finley. Valerie moves out and pressures Ray into an affair, while his mother covers for him. Andrea's relationship with Jesse is unaffected by meeting Peter and his wife.

Name: Breast Side Up
Description: Donna invites NFL quarterback Steve Young over for Thanksgiving, but learns that she and Joe disapprove of premarital sex. Brandon and Kelly's old feelings return as they miss Susan and Colin. Steve becomes a hit at Clare's father's party. Valerie doesn't want cooking help from David's mother.

Name: Angels We Have Heard on High
Description: Cindy returns to Beverly Hills for Christmas without Jim, while Colin's drug use puts a strain on his relationship with Kelly. Joe gives Donna a talking parrot for her birthday. Steve loses his job due to someone else's mistake, causing tension with his father Rush.

Name: Turn Back the Clock
Description: The gang shares New Year's mishap stories, including Steve babysitting his rowdy stepbrothers at the After Dark. Kelly and Colin's relationship is strained by his drug use, and Jonathan Casten's arrival causes problems between Susan and Brandon.

Name: Bleeding Hearts
Description: Clare bets Steve he won't stay celibate at a Valentine's Day party. Valerie's plan to keep David away from Ginger fails, causing David to leave her. Kelly hits rock bottom after getting beaten up while buying cocaine. Joe is kicked off the football team due to his heart disorder.

Name: Fearless
Description: Steve tries to make Clare jealous by dating someone else, while Donna's new boyfriend, Cliff, helps her with a Halloween party. Valerie resorts to her devious ways to avoid Kenny, and Kelly and Brandon have their own romantic pursuits.

Name: Gift Wrapped
Description: Valerie and Kelly exchange Christmas gifts, with Kelly discovering a surprise half-sister, Joy. Steve and Clare play matchmaker for their parents. David tries to impress Donna's conservative mother. Brandon and Tracy exchange gifts.

Name: My Funny Valentine
Description: Donna's ex-boyfriend causes trouble, while Valerie's mother visits and asks for money. Steve smokes pot with a guy he dislikes. David and Chloe perform at a Valentine's Day party. Kelly continues dating Tom, and Valerie tries to stop it.

Name: You Say Goodbye, I Say Hello
Grandma Got Run Over By a Reindeer
Every Day Is a Holiday (With You)
It Came Upon a Midnight Clear
I'd Like to Start with the Cat
On Vodka, on Soda, on Blender, on Mixer!
It's the Most Wonderful Time of the Year
Christmas Comes This Time Each Year
Have Yourself a Very Little Christmas
Christmas Comes But Once a Year
Do You Fear What I Fear?
Would You Like a Drumstick or a Kidney?
George Is Being Elfish and Christ-misses His Family
I'm Scheming of a White Christmas
The Wood, the Bad and the Hungry
Santa's Got a Brand New Bag
House of Horrors with Formal Dining and Used Brick
Bar Wars V: The Final Judgement
Caroline and the Used Car Salesman
Caroline and the Fright Before Christmas
Now You See It, Now You Don't: Part 1
Now You See It, Now You Don't: Part 2
The Gift of the Mike Guy
Let It Snow, Let It Snow, Let It Snow... Dammit
I'm Dreaming of a Holiday Episode
Why Do Fools Fall in Love?
What Are You Doing New Year's Eve?
Jingle Hell, Jingle Hell, Jingle All the Way
I'm Dreaming of a Brown Christmas
Halloween 4: The Revenge of Rod Skyhook
It's the Great Pumpkin, Phil Dunphy
The Days of Wine and Vodka
Peggy Loves Al - Yeah, Yeah, Yeah
He Is Risen
Description: Tony and Ralphie's animosity intensifies until they are forced to confront each other. Meadow starts dating Jackie's son and finds herself in a dangerous situation.

Name: To Save Us All from Satan's Power
Description: Tony experiences flashbacks of Pussy's betrayal and grows concerned about Jackie Jr.'s failure to meet his responsibilities.

Name: Kaisha
Description: Tony and Phil clash, resulting in Phil's hospitalization. Meanwhile, Tony and Christopher find themselves romantically involved with the same woman.

Name: Hungry Man
Description: Dexter delves deeper into Arthur's dark psyche while Rita prepares Thanksgiving dinner for their guests. Debra investigates Trinity, and Batista closes an old case.

Name: Do You See What I See?
Description: Dexter struggles to balance his life with Hannah and his relationship with Debra, as Christmas draws near. Meanwhile, he discovers that the man behind his mother's murder has been released from prison.

Name: The Middle Earth Paradigm
Description: The guys attend Penny's Halloween party, but Leonard has a tense encounter with Penny's ex-boyfriend Kurt.

Name: The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
Description: Leonard becomes jealous when Penny takes an interest in a handsome physicist at the university. Meanwhile, Sheldon struggles to choose the perfect Christmas gift for Penny.

Name: The Maternal Congruence
Description: Leonard's mother pays a visit, much to Leonard's chagrin and Sheldon's excitement

Name: The Large Hadron Collision
Description: Leonard is invited to visit the CERN laboratory in Switzerland on Valentine's Day, and Sheldon competes with Penny to be his guest.

Name: The Good Guy Fluctuation
Description: Sheldon tries to scare the gang after they play a prank on him for Halloween. Leonard seeks Penny's advice when an attractive comic book artist shows interest in him.

Name: The Holographic Excitation
Description: Raj organizes Stuart's Halloween party at the comic book store while Howard's constant talk about space annoys the gang. Meanwhile, Penny makes an effort to take an interest in Leonard's work.

Name: The Santa Simulation
Description: The girls take Raj out to a nightclub to help him find a date. Meanwhile, a game of Dungeons and Dragons brings back memories of Santa Claus for Sheldon.

Name: The Tangible Affection Proof
Description: Sheldon enlists Alex's help to buy a Valentine's Day gift for Amy. Leonard, Penny, Howard, and Bernadette have a disastrous dinner together. Raj and Stuart host a "Lonely People" party at the comic book store

Name: The Thanksgiving Decoupling
Description: The gang decides to spend Thanksgiving at Mrs. Wolowitz's house, but Sheldon is unhappy about the holiday, and tensions rise when Penny's ex-boyfriend shows up.

Name: The Cooper Extraction
Description: Sheldon goes back home to Texas for the holidays. The absence of Sheldon causes the group to appreciate his unique personality and contribution to their friendships.

Name: The Locomotive Manipulation
Description: Sheldon and Amy go on a train ride to Napa Valley with Howard and Bernadette for Valentine's Day. Meanwhile, Leonard and Penny take care of Raj's dog.

Name: The Clean Room Infiltration
Description: Amy hosts a traditional Victorian Christmas Eve dinner for the gang, while Raj's father visits from India. The guys try to get rid of a bird they accidentally let into the university clean room.

Name: The Platonic Permutation
Description: Sheldon and Amy try to spend time together as friends and visit an aquarium on Thanksgiving. Howard agrees to volunteer at the soup kitchen with Bernadette, Raj, and Emily.

Name: The Valentino Submergence
Description: Sheldon and Amy host a Valentine's Day edition of "Fun with Flags". Leonard and Penny come to terms with the challenges of aging. Meanwhile, Howard and Bernadette discover a surprise in their hot tub.

Name: The Holiday Summation
Description: The gang share stories about their holiday breaks. Sheldon and Amy talk about their trip to Texas, Leonard and Penny share their Christmas tree adventure, and Howard and Bernadette discuss their experiences as new parents.

Name: The Imitation Perturbation
Description: Wolowitz dresses up as Sheldon for Halloween and Sheldon seeks revenge. Leonard is surprised when Penny doesn't remember their first kiss.

Name: That Holiday Spirit
Description: Dominique joins the Carringtons for a Christmas gala. The party is highlighted by an announcement from Blake, which draws a lot of attention.

Name: Escape from Witch Island
Description: Dawson enlists friends to shoot a documentary for history class about a local haunted spot. As they work, tales of love and witches make Dawson and Joey reflect on their relationship while Jen and Pacey develop a new bond.

Name: Guess Who's Coming to Dinner
Description: On Thanksgiving Jen's mother arrives, leading Dawson to confront her about her secret past. He tries to bring Jen and her mother closer. Gail is frustrated with Grams taking over cooking.

Name: Valentine's Day Massacre
Description: Joey questions Dawson's judgment when he and Pacey lead their friends to a secret party on a golf course hosted by a wealthy and snobbish student.

Name: Self Reliance
Description: Joey struggles to find time to study when Bessie goes on a weekend getaway, as she juggles responsibilities at the B&B and Pacey's advances. Dealing with her emotions about Dawson kissing Gretchen at the Christmas party.

Name: Four Scary Stories
Description: Joey, Jack, and Pacey share scary stories at Grams' house after watching a disappointing horror film. Joey recounts a spooky incident at the library on Halloween night while studying alone.

Name: Living Dead Girl
Description: Dawson sees a ghostly apparition and suspects Todd's up to something at his Halloween costume party. Meanwhile, Jack encourages Jen to call C.J., but when he shows up at the party with another guy, Jen thinks he's gay.

Name: Merry Mayhem
Description: Dawson returns to Capeside for Christmas. He struggles with his feelings about Natasha's relationship with Max, while Todd's drinking concerns Gail. Joey arrives with Audrey, and Eddie surprises them with a Christmas tree.

Name: The Prank King
Description: Dre worries that his family's Halloween tradition of playing outrageous pranks on each other will be ruined when his older children refuse to participate.

Name: Black Santa/White Christmas
Description: Dre wants to have a black Santa at his office Christmas party, despite HR already assigning the role. Meanwhile, Bow doesn't want to compete with Ruby for cooking the holiday dinner.

Name: Big Night, Big Fight
Description: Dre strives to maintain harmony on Valentine's Day while Diane's brothers and sisters endeavor to teach her the art of giving compliments.

Name: Jacked o' Lantern
Description: Dre's children are disappointed when their cousins come to the neighborhood to trick-or-treat; Dre also has to face his childhood bully, his cousin June Bug.

Name: Stuff
Description: Dre wants to reduce the commercialization of Christmas and spend more time together. His parents suggest cutting down on gifts but the kids don't agree.

Name: The Purge
Description: Dre teaches his son a lesson in pranking after being embarrassed during a basketball game. Meanwhile, the neighborhood participates in mischief night for Halloween, where petty crimes are allowed.

Name: Auntsgiving
Description: Pops' sister Almaviligerais shows up for Thanksgiving, much to everyone's delight except Ruby. While Bow and Dre go on vacation, the kids try to uncover why Ruby has a grudge against Almaviligerais.

Name: Just Christmas, Baby
Description: Dre aims to make a memorable Christmas for his family as Zoey prepares to leave for college. Meanwhile, Bow takes care of Gigi's newborn and realizes the challenges of motherhood.

Name: Scarred for Life
Description: The twins refuse to participate in the family Halloween costume, worrying it will ruin their social standing in school. To help them, Dre and Bow create a haunted house and invite their entire seventh-grade class.

Name: Christmas in Theater Eight
Description: The Johnson family struggles to agree on which movie to watch during their annual Christmas theater trip. Junior feels embarrassed when his ex mistakes him for a theater employee.

Name: Dreamgirls and Boys
Description: Dre and Bow deal with identity politics, Diane faces heartbreak as her crush starts spending time with another girl, and Junior's Valentine's Day date goes wrong after a talk about chivalry.

Name: Everybody Blames Raymond
Description: The Johnsons clash over the family Halloween costume and try to make Devante's first trick-or-treating experience perfect. They also try to get rid of Jack's new friend Raymond.

Name: Father Christmas
Description: Pops surprises Dre with holiday cheer, but a visitor from Lynette's past dampens the family's holiday spirit.

Name: The Gauntlet
Description: Dre struggles to find the perfect Valentine's Day gift for Bow, while Ruby's outdated dating advice fails to help Jack with his love problems.

Name: Compton Around the Christmas Tree
Description: Dre takes his family to his hometown of Compton to reconnect with his roots, but Bow has an idea to teach the kids about the spirit of giving by having them volunteer.

Name: Santa's Little Helper
Description: Cory tries to get Shawn a present after his dad gets laid off at Christmas. Morgan is traumatized when Santa Claus has a heart attack.

Name: Who's Afraid of Cory Wolf?
Description: Cory thinks he might be a werewolf after being bitten by an animal, and a fortune teller confirms it. She warns him of three prophecies, one involving killing a girl who loves him.

Name: Train of Fools
Description: The teens are stranded without transportation and end up spending New Year's Eve in an abandoned subway car.

Name: Turkey Day
Description: Cory and Shawn try to promote unity between their families by suggesting they celebrate Thanksgiving together after learning about tribal prejudices in Africa.

Name: Easy Street
Description: Cory gets a job at a Mafia-controlled restaurant but quits when he finds out. Shawn takes the job instead to earn money for Christmas.

Name: A Long Walk to Pittsburgh: Part 1
Description: Shawn kisses Topanga on the cheek and Eric tells Cory, causing tension. When Cory learns Topanga is moving away, he realizes his priorities.

Name: A Long Walk to Pittsburgh: Part 2
Description: Topanga runs away from home in the rain to convince her parents to let her live with an aunt in town. Cory and Topanga must prove their love to their parents.

Name: The Witches of Pennbrook
Description: Jack prioritizes his new girlfriend over his friendship with Eric, who uncovers that she's a witch. While Eric tries to warn Jack, Topanga conquers her fear of flying during a trip to Pittsburgh with Cory.

Name: Chasing Angela: Part 2
Description: Shawn confesses to Cory about his feelings for Angela after a mix-up with a lost purse, but is uncertain if Angela feels the same way. Meanwhile, Eric and Jack host Thanksgiving dinner for the Matthews family in their new apartment.

Name: A Very Topanga Christmas
Description: Cory invites Topanga to spend Christmas with his family, but they clash over their differing holiday traditions, causing Cory to question their future together.

Name: First Girlfriends' Club
Description: Shawn's ex-girlfriends kidnap him on Valentine's Day to prevent him from hurting Angela, convinced that he will ruin their relationship. Meanwhile, Topanga reads a letter from Lauren and Cory must face the consequences.

Name: Santa's Little Helpers
Description: Cory and Topanga confront the fact that Shawn and Angela still have feelings for each other, but they disagree on how to handle the situation.

Name: My Baby Valentine
Description: Cory plans a baby shower for Amy, but it turns out to be a disaster. Amy goes into premature labor, and the family rushes to the hospital. Meanwhile, Shawn is lost and Morgan is unhappy about the new baby. Jack and Rachel worry about Eric's reaction to their relationship.

Name: The First Thanksgiving
Description: Dharma tries to cook Thanksgiving dinner while Kitty makes a restaurant reservation as a backup plan.

Name: Haus Arrest
Description: Dharma struggles to take care of Greg's teenage cousin, Jennifer.

Name: Dharma and Greg's First Romantic Valentine's Day Weekend
Description: Greg's plan for a romantic weekend getaway goes awry, leaving him and his partner disappointed. Meanwhile, Kitty suspects that Larry may be interested in mate-swapping.

Name: See Dharma Run
Description: Dharma receives a parking ticket while feeding expired meters out of kindness, which leads her to run for the Board of Supervisors. Meanwhile, Jane and Pete tie the knot on Valentine's Day.

Name: The Very Grateful Dead
Description: Dharma channels the spirit of a deceased neighbor woman who lived an unfulfilled life, leading her to confront the regrets she has in her own life.

Name: Thanksgiving Until It Hurts
Description: Greg and Dharma struggle to balance Thanksgiving celebrations hosted by both their families. Abby has a breakdown over preparing the turkey, and Kitty's cooking is a disaster.

Name: The Trouble with Troubador
Description: Bob Dylan calls Dharma while Greg is in the middle of confirming their Valentine's weekend plans, surprising Greg that they were already friends from playing music together.

Name: Used Karma
Description: Dharma buys a haunted sports car previously owned by a gangster named Shorty Green. Meanwhile, Edward hires a security professional to catch the Halloween egg thrower at his house.

Name: Wish We Weren't Here
Description: Greg and Dharma's Thanksgiving Bahamas trip is cancelled due to bad weather, leaving them stranded in Fort Wayne. While Greg tries to rebook their flights, Dharma helps a couple save their relationship before their wedding.

Name: The Christmas Episode
Description: Stabler enlists Benson and the task force to find his missing son Eli, while Wheatley contemplates his future.

Name: Last Christmas
Description: A unit of police officers is closing down when they receive an offer from Robert Silas to surrender and cooperate. As they head to meet him, they discover they are not the only ones looking for him.

Name: Fucksgiving
Description: Piper reconciles with Alex and prepares for a visit from Larry on Thanksgiving. But when Piper is sent to solitary confinement for dancing with Alex, she confronts harsh realities and reevaluates her life choices.

Name: Can't Fix Crazy
Description: Red's kitchen plan fails, inmates stage a Christmas pageant, and Piper's safety is threatened, leading her to reassess her plans.

Name: You Also Have a Pizza
Description: The inmates get ready for a Valentine's Day party and love is in the air. Red makes an intriguing discovery and Larry approaches Piper to be his prison mole.
